Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Bug (item 6): the ship search <datalist> put size/class as each
<option>'s visible text content and the ship name only in its value
attribute. Some browsers (reported: ships showing as just their class)
render an option's text content as the primary label in the
autocomplete UI, not the value — so the searchable ship name was
effectively hidden. Fixed by making the ship name lead the visible
text: 'Behemoth Vanguard — L Destroyer'. Verified the underlying value
(what actually fills the input on selection) was already correct.

Feature (item 7): the side picker no longer defaults to a generated
role build when the ship has saved loadouts — it now prefers the
user's own saved build first, role builds second, stock last. This
needed a fresh (non-memoized) read of saved builds at pick-time, since
the existing  useMemo is still keyed to the previous ship for
one render after picking a new one.

Added an empty-state notice ('No saved load outs for X yet.' + a
'+ Create load out' button) when the selected ship has zero saved
builds, wired through a new onOpenFitting prop (CombatView -> App.tsx)
that navigates straight to the Fitting screen for that ship — same
pattern ShipBrowser's onOpen already uses.
